@(1-14=c131.C.1) @q[,]{“…… she will drink, …… she will eat. Come here! ……. I will ……, …… do. The maiden …… the @fsux{abzu} and @wSN{Eridug}, @wDN{Inana} …… the @fsux{abzu} and @wSN{Eridug} ……. When the maiden @wDN{Inana} has entered the @fsux{abzu} and @wSN{Eridug}, when @wDN{Inana} has entered the @fsux{abzu} and @wSN{Eridug}, offer her butter cake to eat. Let her be served cool refreshing water. Pour beer for her, in front of the Lions' Gate, make her feel as if she is in her girlfriend's house, make her …… as a colleague. You are to welcome holy @wDN{Inana} at the holy table, at the table of @wDN{An}.”


@(15-26=c131.C.15) After @wDN{Enki} had spoken thus to him, @wDN{Isimud} the minister followed his master's instructions closely. He let the maiden into the @fsux{abzu} and @wSN{Eridug}. He let @wDN{Inana} into the @fsux{abzu} and @wSN{Eridug}. When the maiden had entered the @fsux{abzu} and @wSN{Eridug}, when @wDN{Inana} had entered the @fsux{abzu} and @wSN{Eridug}, she got butter cake to eat. They poured cool refreshing water for her, and they gave her beer to drink, in front of the Lions' Gate. He made her feel as if she was in her girlfriend's house, and made her …… as a colleague. He welcomed holy @wDN{Inana} at the holy table, at the table of @wDN{An}.

@(27-30=c131.C.27) So it came about that @wDN{Enki} and @wDN{Inana} were drinking beer together in the @fsux{abzu}, and enjoying the taste of sweet wine. The bronze @fsux{aga} vessels were filled to the brim, and the two of them started a competition, drinking from the bronze vessels of @wDN{Uraš}.
