@(1-7=c131.H.1) The prince spoke to his minister @wDN{Isimud}, @wDN{Enki} addressed the Sweet Name of Heaven: @q[Enki,Isimud]{“@wDN{Isimud}, my minister, my Sweet Name of Heaven!” @q[Isimud,Enki]{“@wDN{Enki}, my master, I am at your service! What is your wish?” @q[Enki,Isimud]{“Where has the Boat of Heaven reached now?” @q[Isimud,Enki]{“It has just now reached the …… Quay.” @q[Enki,Isimud]{“Go now! The @fsux{enkum} are to take the Boat of Heaven away from her!”

@(8-19=c131.H.8) The minister @wDN{Isimud} spoke to holy @wDN{Inana}: @q[Isimud,Inana]{“My lady! Your father has sent me to you. @wDN{Inana}, your father has sent me to you. What your father said was very serious. What @wDN{Enki} spoke was very serious. His important words cannot be countermanded.” Holy @wDN{Inana} replied to him: @q[Inana,Isimud]{“What has my father said to you, what has he spoken? Why should his important words not be countermanded?” @q[Isimud,Inana]{“My master has spoken to me, @wDN{Enki} has said to me: @q[Enki,Isimud]{“@wDN{Inana} may travel to @wSN{Unug}, but you are to get the Boat of Heaven back to @wSN{Eridug} for me”.”

@(20-33=c131.H.20) Holy @wDN{Inana} spoke to the minister @wDN{Isimud}: @q[Inana,Isimud]{“How could my father have changed what he said to me? How could he have altered his promise as far as I am concerned? How could he have discredited his important words to me? Was it falsehood that my father said to me, did he speak falsely to me? Has he sworn falsely by the name of his power and by the name of his @fsux{abzu}? Has he duplicitously sent you to me as a messenger?” Now as these words were still in her mouth, he got the @fsux{enkum} to seize hold of the Boat of Heaven. Holy @wDN{Inana} adressed her minister @wDN{Ninšubur}: @q[Inana,Nincubur]{“Come, my good minister of @wTN{E-ana}! My fair-spoken minister! My envoy of reliable words! Water has never touched your hand, water has never touched your feet!”

